<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3858269>
    dc:description "Fig. 52. Bracon (Glabrobracon) caudiger Nees, 1834 (A-G: ♀ neotype, H-K: ♀ / ♁). A. Head in dorsal view. B. Head in frontal view. C. Hind femur. D. Claw. E. Distal part of right forewing. F. First discal cell of right forewing. G. Tergites 1-3. H. Head in dorsal view. I-J. Hind femur. K. First tergite." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3858269/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3858271>
    dc:description "Fig. 53. — A-D. Bracon (Glabrobracon) xanthogaster Nees, 1834, ♀. A. Tergites 1-3. B. Head in dorsal view. C. Head in lateral view. D. Claw. — E. Bracon (Glabrobracon) caudiger Nees, 1834, ♀ / ♁, head in lateral view. — F-I. Bracon (Glabrobracon) pineti Thomson, 1894, ♀. F. Tergites 1-3. G. Head in dorsal view. H. Hind half of head in dorsal view. I. Claw." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3858271/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3858273>
    dc:description "Fig. 54. Bracon (Palpibracon) delibator Haliday, 1833 (A-J: ♀ neotype, K-M: ♀). A. Flagellomeres 1-2 and 17-19. B. Head in dorsal view. C. Head in lateral view. D. Head in frontal view. E. Ultimate three segments of maxillar palp. F. Hind femur. G. Claw. H. Distal part of right forewing. I. First discal cell of right forewing. J. Tergites 1-3. K. Ultimate three segments of maxillar palp (♀ / ♁). L. Hind femur. M. First tergite." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3858273/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3858275>
    dc:description "Fig. 55. — A-G. Bracon (Palpibracon) delibator Haliday, 1833 (A-D: ♀, E-G: ♁). A. First discal cell of right forewing. B. First tergite. C-D. Tergites 2-3. E-F. First tergite. G. Tergites 2-3. — H-K. Bracon (Palpibracon) atrator Nees, 1834, ♀ neotype. H. Tergites 1-3. I. Distal part of right forewing. J. Ultimate three segments of maxillar palp (1 = neotype, 2 = ♀ / ♁), K. Head in frontal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3858275/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3858277>
    dc:description "Fig. 56. — A-C. Bracon (Palpibarcon) mongolicus Telenga, 1936, ♀. A. Tergites 1-3. B. Distal part of right forewing. C. Head in frontal view. — D-F. Bracon (Palpibracon) tenuiceps Muesebeck, 1925, ♀. D. Tergites 1-3. E. Distal part of right forewing. F. Ultimate three segments of maxillar palp. — G-I. Bracon (Palpibracon) delibator Haliday, 1833 (G: ♀ / ♁, H-I: ♀). G. Hind half of head in dorsal view. H-I. First submarginal cell of right forewing." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3858277/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

